            <title>[DERBY-3492] When the replication log buffer becomes full, the chunk of log that should be appended is to the buffer is discarded</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/DERBY-3492</link>
                <project id="10594" key="DERBY">Derby</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;In MasterController#appendLog, log is force-sent to the slave if the replication log buffer becomes full. However, the log chunk that should have been appended is discarded:&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;try {&lt;br/&gt;
     logBuffer.appendLog(greatestInstant, log, logOffset, logLength);&lt;br/&gt;
} catch (LogBufferFullException lbfe) {&lt;br/&gt;
     try &lt;/p&gt;
{
         logShipper.forceFlush();
     }
&lt;p&gt; catch (IOException ioe) {&lt;br/&gt;
...&lt;br/&gt;
}&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;The log chunk must be added after freeing a log buffer by calling forceFlush&lt;/p&gt;</description>
