                            <comment id="12575019" author="jorgenlo" created="Tue, 4 Mar 2008 15:22:58 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Patch 1a appends the log chunk to the replication log buffer after forcing a log shipment to the slave. &lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Without the patch, replication consistently fails with a &quot;ERROR XRE05: The log files on the master and slave are not in synch...&quot; exception a few seconds after forceFlush is called (reproduce by starting a transaction with &lt;b&gt;many&lt;/b&gt; inserts or deletes; exception only written to derby.log on slave). With the patch, I have not been able to reproduce the bug.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;All tests passed (with the exception of TransactionTable.sql which also fails in tinderbox). Request for review.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="12575292" author="oysteing" created="Wed, 5 Mar 2008 10:16:52 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Patch looks good.  I am not able to reproduce the issue anymore.&lt;br/&gt;
Committed as revision 633807.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
